# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-

__version__ = "0.2.0"

class Resources:
    @classmethod
    def to_file(cls, name, path):
        from.base64_9 import Base64
        from .os9 import OS
        string = cls.resources_dict[f"{name.lower()}_{OS.name}_{OS.architecture}"]
        return Base64.to_file(string, path)

class Resources (*args, **kwargs)

class Resources:
    @classmethod
    def to_file(cls, name, path):
        from.base64_9 import Base64
        from .os9 import OS
        string = cls.resources_dict[f"{name.lower()}_{OS.name}_{OS.architecture}"]
        return Base64.to_file(string, path)

Static methods

def to_file(name, path)
Source code 
@classmethod
def to_file(cls, name, path):
    from.base64_9 import Base64
    from .os9 import OS
    string = cls.resources_dict[f"{name.lower()}_{OS.name}_{OS.architecture}"]
    return Base64.to_file(string, path)
